I love this. You can see the Buddhist influence in bell hooks writing here. Before starting this book, I had a very basic idea of her thoughts and life. There was a quote earlier in the book that I sent to a friend and said this sounds very Buddhist but I don't know if she's actually Buddhist. Then a few pages later, she talked about the influence of Buddhism on her life. How have I slept on these books for so long?
